<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/styles.css"></head><body class="usual"><div class="navline"><a href="/hackchallenge.php" title="Go to the challenge-list."><img src="/files/images/icons/list_small.gif" width="12" height="11" alt="icon" title="Go to the challenge-list." /><span>Challenges</span></a><img src="/files/images/misc/arrow_navline.gif" class="arrow" width="10" height="9" alt="-&gt;" title="" /><span>Science</span><img src="/files/images/misc/arrow_navline.gif" class="arrow" width="10" height="9" alt="-&gt;" title="" /><a href="/challenges/math2/math2.php" title="Challenge: &quot;Geometry&quot;"><span>Geometry</span></a></div><div class="module"><div class="chall_header"><table cellspacing="0"><tr><td class="info"><img class="grouppic" alt="a Science-challenge" src="/files/images/groupmasters/11_all.gif" height="18" width="25" /><span>Science 2: &quot;Geometry&quot;</span></td><td class="links"><table cellspacing="0"><tr><td class="forum"><a href="/challvote.php?challid=100" title="Rate this challenge!"><img src="/files/images/icons/vote_stat_sl.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="vote icon" title="Rate this challenge!" /><span>Vote</span></a></td><td class="forum_space">&nbsp;</td><td class="forum"><a href="/forum/forum_showforum.php?forumid=29&amp;challenge_id=100" title="Visit the Science-Forum to ask questions or to find hints for this challenge."><img src="/files/images/misc/challenge_forum_questions.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="forum icon" title="Visit the Science-Forum to ask questions or to find hints for this challenge." /><span>Forum</span></a></td><td class="forum_space">&nbsp;</td><td class="forum"><a href="/forum/forum_showforum.php?forumid=40&amp;challenge_id=100" title="Visit the Science-Forum for solutions of this challenge."><img src="/files/images/misc/challenge_forum_solutions.gif" width="16" height="16" alt="forum icon" title="Visit the Science-Forum for solutions of this challenge." /><span>Solutions</span></a></td><td class="done">done&nbsp;<a href="/challengestats.php?challengeid=100" title="467 users have solved this challenge so far.">[467]</a></td></tr></table></td></tr></table></div><div class="challenge_div">Given is a square (the stripe-filled polygon), whoose edges have a length of &quot;a&quot; each. A circle with the midpoint M<sub>2</sub> has three points in common with the square-edges:<div class="challenge_1" style="text-align:center;"><img class="challenge_1" src="math2.png" alt="sketch" /></div><span style="text-decoration:overline;">CP</span> has a length of a/4 and M<sub>1</sub> is the midpoint of the squares left edge. What you have to do:<p class="challenge_1" style="text-align:center;">Calculate x (the length of <span style="text-decoration:overline;">PQ</span>) in dependency of the squares edge-length &quot;a&quot;. This means you have to work in general terms. Also the solution, which is the simplified term which expresses &quot;x&quot;, has to be <span style="font-weight:700;">exact</span>, meaning that it mustn't contain any rounded values etc. Additionally, you mustn't use any trigonometric functions in this expression.</p>The solution is the term expressing &quot;x&quot; in a/the simplified manner. If you think your solution is right but you can't figure out the correct way to enter it, <a class="challenge_1" href="/forum/forum_newtopic.php?forumid=50&amp;challenge=100">post it here!</a>
